# First-order TDPT

Let us consider the transition amplityude between orthogonal eigenstates of $H_0$ $\ket{i}$ and $\ket{f \neq i}$. At first order in perturbation theory, the transition amplitude is
```{math}
\begin{align}
{\tilde c}_{fi} & = \bra{f}\left({\bf 1} - \frac{i\eps}{\hbar} \int_0^t dt' V_I(t')\right) \ket{i}\\
& = - \frac{i\eps}{\hbar} \int_0^t dt' \bra{f} V_I(t') \ket{i}
\end{align}
```
